# Privacy Policy for YouTube Layout Adjuster for Brave

**Last Updated:** April 28, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how **YouTube Layout Adjuster for Brave** handles user data.

### Information We Collect
- We do **not** collect any personal information.
- We do **not** track your browsing history, YouTube activity, search queries, or any other data.
- The only information stored is your **user preferences** (whether the customization is enabled and which sections — “Most relevant”, “Live”, and “Shorts” — to hide on the YouTube homepage and subscriptions page).  
  These settings are saved **locally on your device** using the browser’s `chrome.storage` API and never leave your computer.

### Data Sharing
We do not share, sell, transmit, or send any data to third parties, external servers, or even the developer.

### Data Storage
All data is stored **only on your device**. You can clear it anytime by clearing your browser’s extension data or resetting the extension options.

### Third-Party Services
This extension does not use any third-party services or APIs. It only modifies the YouTube website (https://www.youtube.com) locally in your browser.

### Security
No data is transmitted over the internet. The extension operates entirely client-side.

### User Rights
Since no personal data is collected or retained, there is no mechanism needed to access, modify, or delete data. You can disable or uninstall the extension at any time via your browser’s Extensions menu.

### Policy Updates
We may update this policy if the extension changes. The latest version will always be available at this URL.

**Contact**  
If you have any questions or concerns, feel free to open an issue on the extension’s GitHub repository (link will be provided in the Chrome Web Store listing).

This policy complies with Chrome Web Store requirements and applicable privacy laws.
